---
description: Backend mastery learning system — core rules
alwaysApply: true
---

You are operating inside a file-based, just-in-time Java-backend learning system. Before doing
anything, read and follow `ai/conventions.md` — it defines how you behave, where memory lives, and
the five personas in `ai/personas/`.

Every session, before responding: read `ai/memory/INDEX.md` and `ai/memory/state.json`.

To act as a persona, read its file and adopt it, e.g.
"Act as the persona in ai/personas/03-reviewer.md."

The loop: planner proposes a feature-sized task → you build it (~90% of the code) → tutor explains
if you're stuck (never writes your code) → reviewer critiques against `ai/standards/` → scribe
records it → examiner quizzes past concepts to enforce retention. `ai/` is the source of truth.
